\hspace{0cm}{\color{mediumblue}{\zitiAa\heiti 概况~}}
中国森林生物多样性监测网络（Sino BON-CForBio）是基于中国植被区划成果而设计和构建的全国性森林监测样地网络，是全球森林生物多样性监测网络（CTFS-ForestGEO）中最活跃的区域网络（图1）。到2016年，该网络包括在中国不同气候带典型森林植被区域建立的18个大型森林样地（总面积为367公顷）；监测胸径大于1cm的木本植物超过1,600种、160万株；监测森林类型包括北方林、针阔混交林、落叶阔叶林、常绿落叶阔叶混交林、常绿阔叶林以及热带雨林（图2$-$7）。基于该网络跨气候带谱的数据，在国际主流生态学期刊如Ecology Letters、Ecology等发表学术论文378篇，其中SCI论文196篇，特别是关于森林群落物种共存机理的研究成果，被国外同行在Nature等顶级期刊积极评价。
%
\\[1.1cm]
%
{\color{mediumblue}{\zitiAa\phv Overview~}}
\zitiA
Chinese Forest Biodiversity Monitoring Network (Sino BON-CForBio) is a national forest monitoring network, designed and built on the basis of Chinese forest region and forest zone (Figure 1). It is the most active regional network of Forest Global Earth Observatory networks (CTFS-Forest GEO). 
By the end of 2016, Sino BON-CForBio comprises 18 forest dynamics plots with a total area of 367 hm$\sffamily^\num{2}$, monitors over 1.6 million trees individuals belonging to 1,600 woody species, and covers zonal forest types in major climate zones in China, including cold temperate boreal forests, temperate coniferous and broadleaved mixed forests, warm temperate deciduous broadleaved forests, subtropical evergreen broadleaved forests, and tropical rain forests (Figure 2--7). Based on data cross climatic spectrum in Sino BON-CForBio, 378 scientific articles have been published, including 196 SCI papers, which were published in the mainstream journals, such as Ecology Letters, Ecology and so on. The research results on the mechanism of species coexistence were given positive evaluations in Nature Journal by colleagues worldwide.
